<!-- Tuple Pattern -->
	<section xml:id="ref.patterns.tuple">
		<title>Tuple Pattern</title>
		<section xml:id="ref.patterns.tuple.body">
			<para>
				In Orc pattern matching, when a value is compared to a tuple, the entire tuple must
				be matched exactly to be considered a successful pattern match.
			</para>
			<para><emphasis role="strong">EBNF</emphasis>: <emphasis>P ::= <code>( P , ... , P )</code></emphasis></para>
		</section>
		
		 <section xml:id="ref.patterns.tuple.examples">
		  <title>Examples</title>

		  <example xml:id="ref.patterns.tuple.examples.one"><title>Filtering</title>
<programlisting language="orc-demo"><![CDATA[
{- Signal for each of the input tuples that have their first value as true -}
{- Should publish one signal -}
(false, true, true) | (true, false, false) | (false, false, false) >(true, _, _)> signal
]]></programlisting>
		  </example>
		</section>
		
